      <td>Automated multi-layer (reduced 40-60%)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Bugs escaping to production</td>
      <td>Computation + architecture bugs ship</td>
      <td>Caught at build/PR time</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>CI reliability</td>
      <td>84% flaky failure rate</td>
      <td>&lt;2% flakiness budget with quarantine</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Developer trust in CI</td>
      <td>Low &mdash; merge without waiting</td>
      <td>High &mdash; failures mean real problems</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Architecture compliance</td>
      <td>Manual code review (inconsistent)</td>
      <td>Automated gate (deterministic)</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Deployment timeline</h2>

<Timeline />

<Callout type="info" title="No big bang required">
  <p>
    Visdom Testing layers are additive. You don't rewrite your test suite. You add architecture rules,
    property-based tests, and mutation analysis on top of what you already have. The pilot starts with
    1-2 modules and expands from there.
  </p>
</Callout>

</DocLayout>
